The '''1989 Summer Deaflympics''', officially known as the '''16th Summer Deaflympics''', is an international [[multi-sport event]] that was held from 7 to 17 January 1989 at [[Queen Elizabeth II Park]] in [[Christchurch]], New Zealand.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Bailey|first1=Joan|title=16th World Games for the Deaf, Christchurch|url=http://signdna.org/video/16th-world-games-for-the-deaf-christchurch/|publisher=Manawatu Deaf Society|accessdate=13 November 2015}}</ref><ref name="Christchurch 1989">{{cite web|title=Christchurch 1989|url=http://www.deaflympics.com/games.asp?1989-s|publisher=[[Comité International des Sports des Sourds]]|accessdate=13 November 2015}}</ref>
