{{Infobox event | title = 2014 Medina hotel fire | image = File:Al Madinah in Saudi Arabia.svg | image_size = 250px | caption = Location of Al Madinah Region in Saudi Arabia | date = {{start date|2014|02|08}} | time = | place = [[Medina, Saudi Arabia|Medina]], [[Al Madinah Region]], [[Saudi Arabia]] | coordinates = | also known as = | cause = Electrical short circuit | reported deaths = 15 | reported injuries = 130 | reported missing = | reported property damage = | notes = }}
The '''2014 Medina hotel fire''' was a hotel fire that occurred in a hotel in [[Medina, Saudi Arabia]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Dhabi|first=Abu|title=Fifteen pilgrims die in Saudi Arabia hotel fire: report|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2014/02/08/us-saudi-fire-idUSBREA170OP20140208|publisher=Reuters|accessdate=9 February 2014}}</ref> The fire killed at least 15 people and another 130 were wounded.
==History== Around seven hundred pilgrims from different countries were staying at the hotel in Medina to perform the [[Umrah]]. An electrical short circuit caused a fire to break out in the hotel. According to a local government statement the fire was first reported at 6:30 pm [[Eastern Time Zone|ET]], and the blaze was contained by 9:00 pm ET.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2014/02/08/world/meast/saudi-arabia-fire/index.html|title=At least 15 killed in hotel fire in Saudi Arabian city of Medina - CNN|last=CNN|first=By Mohammed Jamjoom and Greg Botelho,|work=CNN|access-date=2018-08-29}}</ref> Fifteen Egyptian pilgrims were killed and one hundred and thirty other pilgrims were injured as a result of the fire. Preliminary indications suggested that those who were killed died of [[Asphyxia|suffocation]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.timesofisrael.com/saudi-arabia-fire-at-medina-hotel-kills-15/|title=Saudi Arabia: Fire at Medina hotel kills 15|access-date=2018-08-29|language=en-US}}</ref> The Egyptian consul general in the city of [[Jeddah|Jiddah]], told reporters that most of the injured were Egyptians and that two children were among the dead.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/fire-at-medina-hotel-in-saudi-arabia-kills-15-injures-130-550209|title=Fire at Medina hotel in Saudi Arabia kills 15, injures 130|work=NDTV.com|access-date=2018-08-29}}</ref> It took the rescue teams around two hours to put out the fire completely.<ref>{{cite web|title=At least 15 pilgrims killed in Saudi Arabia hotel fire|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-26105944|publisher=BBC|accessdate=9 February 2014}}</ref>
