'''''American Dreams in China''''' ({{zh|s=中国合伙人|p=Zhōngguó héhuǒ rén|l=Chinese (business) partners}}) is a 2013 Chinese film directed by [[Peter Chan]] and starring [[Huang Xiaoming]], [[Deng Chao]], and [[Tong Dawei]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://movie.mtime.com/174760 |title= 中国合伙人American Dreams in China (2013) |accessdate= 2013-06-14|work= movie.mtime.com|language=Chinese}}</ref> It was shown at the [[2013 Toronto International Film Festival]].<ref name="TIFF2013">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2013/jul/23/toronto-film-festival-lineup |title=Toronto film festival 2013: the full line-up |accessdate=2013-07-24|work=The Guardian|location=London|date=2013-07-23}}</ref> It is based on the story of [[New Oriental]].

==Plot==
Three young men from poor backgrounds achieve success by establishing a reputable English teaching school. 

