{{Infobox civilian attack | title = Cheddikulam massacre | image = | caption = | map = LocationSriLanka.png | map_caption = Location of Sri Lanka | location = [[Cheddikulam]], [[Northern Province, Sri Lanka|Northern Province]], Sri Lanka | coordinates = | target = [[Sri Lankan Tamil]] Civilians | date = December 02, 1984 | time = | timezone = +8 GMT | type = | fatalities = 52 | injuries = Unknown | perps = [[Sri Lankan military]] | susperps = | weapons = }}
The '''Cheddikulam massacre''' was a massacre of [[Sri Lankan Tamil]] civilians in the village of [[Cheddikulam]], located on the border of the [[Vavuniya District|Vavuniya]] and [[Mannar District|Mannar]] districts. It was among the first of the series of massacres carried out by the [[Sri Lankan armed forces]] during the [[Sri Lankan Civil War|country's Civil War]].<ref name="NESHOR">{{cite book| last =| first =| authorlink = NESHOR| title = Massacres of Tamils(1956-2008)| publisher = Manitham Publications| series =| volume = | edition = | location = Chennai| date = 2009| page = 15| doi =| isbn = 978-81-909737-0-0 | mr =| zbl =}}</ref><ref name="COV"/>
==Massacre== On December 2, 1984, the Sri Lankan military imposed a curfew throughout [[Cheddikulam]] and the adjoining villages and towns. The military began cordoning off the village at 5.30 a.m. Most of the its inhabitants were still asleep, when armed personnel entered the village and took away the males of the village for 'inquiries'.<ref name="COV">{{cite web | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=b7F-dUh5_j8C&pg=PA112&lpg=PA112&dq=cheddikulam+massacre&source=bl&ots=0rkBiCVP6d&sig=7GngqakwFPust8jxyvAeeu2STGI&hl=en&sa=X&ei=tMyJUoCDDsizrAfqi4CgCA&ved=0CEYQ6AEwBg#v=onepage&q=cheddikulam%20massacre&f=false | title=Cycles of Violence: Human Rights in Sri Lanka Since the Indo-Sri Lanka Agreement | publisher=Asia Watch Committee | accessdate=18 November 2013}}</ref>
52 men were reportedly bundled into military vehicles, and taken to the [[Anuradhapura District]] and killed. The locals allege that the 52 men were taken to a Sinhalese settlement near [[Medawachchiya]], and were chopped up with sharp knives and later heavy vehicles were run over them. As a result, the villagers say all the 52 men died.<ref name="NESHOR"/>
===Witness Accounts=== T Yesuthasan, teacher at Cheddikulam Mahavidyalayam, says,<ref name="NESHOR"/> {{quote|Following the incident people displaced to Vanni, [[Madhu, Sri Lanka|Madhu]] and [[India]]. Among the 52 people killed were my younger brother, my brother-in-law and two more people in our family.}}
Another resident Mayilvahanam says,<ref name="NESHOR"/> {{quote|On that day many of us ran into the forest and escaped. My home was completely destroyed by the [[Sri Lankan Army]]}}
