ne]], American actor (d. 1978) * 1928 &ndash; [[Sven Davidson]], Swedish-American tennis player (d. 2008) * 1928 &ndash; [[Al Rex]], American musician *[[1929]] &ndash; [[Sofia Muratova]], Russian gymnast (d. 2006) * 1929 &ndash; [[Svein Ellingsen]], Norwegian visual artist and hymnist *[[1930]] &ndash; [[Sam Greenlee]], American author and poet (d. 2014) * 1930 &ndash; [[Naomi Shemer]], Israeli singer-songwriter (d. 2004) *[[1931]] &ndash; [[Frank Ramsey (basketball)|Frank Ramsey]], American basketball player and coach (d. 2018) *[[1932]] &ndash; [[Hubert Reeves]], Canadian-French astrophysicist and author *[[1933]] &ndash; [[David Storey]], English author, playwright, and screenwriter (d. 2017) * 1933 &ndash; [[Piero Manzoni]], Italian artist (d. 1963) *[[1934]] &ndash; [[Peter Gzowski]], Canadian journalist and academic (d. 2002) * 1934 &ndash; [[Gordon Lee (footballer)|Gordon Lee]], English footballer and manager * 1934 &ndash; [[Wole Soyinka]], Nigerian author, poet, and playwright, [[Nobel Prize in Literature|Nobel Prize]] laureate * 1934 &ndash; [[Aleksei Yeliseyev]], Russian engineer and astronaut *[[1935]] &ndash; [[Jack Kemp]], American football player and politician, 9th [[United States Secretary of Housing and Urban Development]] (d. 2009) * 1935 &ndash; [[Earl Lovelace]], Trinidadian journalist, author, and playwright * 1935 &ndash; [[Kurt Westergaard]], Danish cartoonist *[[1936]] &ndash; [[Albert Ayler]], American saxophonist and composer (d. 1970) *[[1937]] &ndash; [[Ghillean Prance]], English botanist and ecologist *[[1939]] &ndash; [[Lambert Jackson Woodburne]], South African admiral (d. 2013) *[[1940]] &ndash; [[Tom Lichtenberg]], American football player and coach (d. 2013) * 1940 &ndash; [[Paul Prudhomme]], American chef and author (d. 2015) * 1940 &ndash; [[Patrick Stewart]], English actor, director, and producer *[[1941]] &ndash; [[Grahame Corling]], Australian cricketer * 1941 &ndash; [[Robert Forster]], American actor and producer * 1941 &nd