'''William Hamman''' (born 1952) is an American pilot. Hamman taught doctors and pilots in [[Milwaukee]]. He also talked to many people at [[seminars]]. He claimed to have a medical and doctoral degree from the [[University of Wisconsin-Madison]], but when his credentials were checked by the Associated Press there wasn't anything stating this. It was discovered in December 2010 that he was not a doctor, one of his colleagues said that he did not need to be a doctor to do his job.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Health/MindMoodNews/fake-cardiologist-william-hamman-duped-real-doctors/story?id=12395288 |title=Fake Cardiologist William Hamman Duped Real Doctors – ABC News |publisher=Abcnews.go.com |date=December 15, 2010 |accessdate=November 10, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-504083_162-20025576-504083.html |title=Fake Michigan Doctor William Hamman Fooled Hospitals for 15 Years – Crimesider |publisher=CBS News |accessdate=November 10, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.healthrelatedinfos.com/william-hamman-fake-doctor-duped-hospital-for-15-years-2457/ |title=William Hamman: Fake Doctor Duped Hospital For 15 Years |publisher=Healthrelatedinfos.com |date=December 15, 2010 |accessdate=November 10, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Travel/renowned-pilot-doctor-exposed-fraud/story?id=12390083 |title=Renowned Pilot, Doctor Exposed as Fraud – ABC News |publisher=Abcnews.go.com |date=December 14, 2010 |accessdate=November 10, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wltx.com/news/story.aspx?storyid=112537 |title=Fake Doctor William Hamman Fooled Hospitals for 15 Years |publisher=wltx.com |date=December 14, 2010 |accessdate=November 10, 2011}}</ref><ref>[https://news.yahoo.com/s/ap/us_med_fake_doctor ] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101216195247/http://news.yahoo.com/s/ap/us_med_fake_doctor |date=December 16, 2010 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Lisa Nainggolan |url=http://www.theheart.org/article/1162023.do |title=Fake cardiologist is exposed as a pilot who flunked medical school |publisher=theheart.org |date=December 13, 2010 |accessdate=November 10, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Marchione |first=Marilynn |url=http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/40630166/ns/health-health_care/ |title=Fake doctor duped hospitals, universities - Health - Health care |publisher=MSNBC |date=March 14, 2010 |accessdate=November 10, 2011}}</ref> Hamman also claimed to have a PhD.<ref>http://www.detnews.com/article/20101215/METRO02/12150355/1409/Hospital-researcher-lied-for-years-about-PhD</ref> Of the six papers he published, one has been retracted.<ref>[http://retractionwatch.wordpress.com/2011/04/13/remember-william-hamman-the-pilot-who-claimed-to-be-a-cardiologist-a-retraction-appears Retraction Watch entry]</ref>

